annotationA: Dynactin 1, p150 subunit (DCTN1-p150) is the p150 subunit of the dynactin complex. Dynactin is thought to act as a dynein receptor that modulates binding of dynein to cellular cargoes and enhances the processivity of dynein movement. DCTN1-p150 roles include oocyte polarity, mitotic cell division, embryonic development, neuronal transport and neurogenesis
annotationB: Dynactin 6, p27 subunit; It is involved in the biological process described with: microtubule-based movement
